OL,6,FFlood definitions may also be unfair
OL,7,Fif they exclude water ingress from
OL,8,Fexternal certain sources, for example
OL,9,Fbecause of non-natural events such as
OL,10,Fa burst water main, the consumer group
OL,11,Fsaid.
OL,13,FWhich? said storm definitions may be
OL,14,Fpotentially unfair if they stipulate a
OL,15,Fsingle type of weather must be
OL,16,Finvolved, such as high winds, or if
OL,17,Fthey exclude certain types of weather
OL,18,Fon its own, such as rain, hail, high
OL,19,Fwind or snow, either explicitly or by
OL,20,Fomission.
