OL,6,FWhich? also carried out a survey of
OL,7,F1,325 people across the UK with
OL,8,Fbuildings insurance, which found more
OL,9,Fthan two-thirds (69%) defined a flood
OL,10,Fas an event where water enters and
OL,11,Fbuilds up in a home regardless of
OL,12,Fspeed, while three-fifths (60%)
OL,13,Fdefined a storm as a combination of
OL,14,Fextreme weather conditions, any of
OL,15,Fwhich could happen alone.
